Definition: chiefly Brit) a council representing employer and employees of a plant or business to discuss working conditions etc
Example: also: a committee representing the workers elected to negotiate with management about grievances and wages etc
Synonyms: council, noun, location, Britain, r, chiefly, Brit, a, representing, employer, and, employees, of, plant, or, business, to, discuss, working, conditions, etc, also, committee, the, workers, elected, negotiate, with, management, about, grievances, wages
Category: noun.group
